 119         def samestat(s1, s2):
 120             """Test whether two stat buffers reference the same file."""
 121             return s1.st_ino == s2.st_ino and s1.st_dev == s2.st_dev
 122 
 123         def samefile(f1, f2):
 124             """Test whether two pathnames reference the same actual file or
 125             directory This is determined by the device number and i-node number
 126             and raises an exception if an os.stat() call on either pathname
 127             fails."""
 128             s1 = os.stat(f1)
 129             s2 = os.stat(f2)
 130             return samestat(s1, s2)

 205 class TemporaryDirectory(object):
 206 
 207     """
 208     Create and return a temporary directory.  This has the same
 209     behavior as mkdtemp but can be used as a context manager.  For
 210     example:
 211 
 212         with TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:
 213             ...
 214 
 215     Upon exiting the context, the directory and everything contained
 216     in it are removed.
 217     """
 218 
 219     def __init__(self, suffix="", prefix=None, dir=None):
 220         if "RAM_DISK" in os.environ:
 221             import uuid
 222 
 223             name = uuid.uuid4().hex
 224             dir_name = os.path.join(os.environ["RAM_DISK"].strip(), name)
 225             os.mkdir(dir_name)
 226             self.name = dir_name
 227         else:
 228             suffix = suffix if suffix else ""
 229             if not prefix:
 230                 self.name = mkdtemp(suffix=suffix, dir=dir)
 231             else:
 232                 self.name = mkdtemp(suffix, prefix, dir)
 233         self._finalizer = finalize(
 234             self,
 235             self._cleanup,
 236             self.name,
 237             warn_message="Implicitly cleaning up {!r}".format(self),
 238         )
 239 
 240     @classmethod
 241     def _rmtree(cls, name):
 242         from .path import rmtree
 243 
 244         rmtree(name)
 245 
 246     @classmethod
 247     def _cleanup(cls, name, warn_message):
 248         cls._rmtree(name)
 249         warnings.warn(warn_message, ResourceWarning)
 250 
 251     def __repr__(self):
 252         return "<{} {!r}>".format(self.__class__.__name__, self.name)
 253 
 254     def __enter__(self):
 255         return self
 256 
 257     def __exit__(self, exc, value, tb):
 258         self.cleanup()
 259 
 260     def cleanup(self):
 261         if self._finalizer.detach():
 262             self._rmtree(self.name)

 265 def is_bytes(string):
 266     """Check if a string is a bytes instance.
 267 
 268     :param Union[str, bytes] string: A string that may be string or bytes like
 269     :return: Whether the provided string is a bytes type or not
 270     :rtype: bool
 271     """
 272     if six.PY3 and isinstance(string, (bytes, memoryview, bytearray)):  # noqa
 273         return True
 274     elif six.PY2 and isinstance(string, (buffer, bytearray)):  # noqa
 275         return True
 276     return False

 279 def fs_str(string):
 280     """Encodes a string into the proper filesystem encoding.
 281 
 282     Borrowed from pip-tools
 283     """
 284 
 285     if isinstance(string, str):
 286         return string
 287     assert not isinstance(string, bytes)
 288     return string.encode(_fs_encoding)

 291 def _get_path(path):
 292     """Fetch the string value from a path-like object.
 293 
 294     Returns **None** if there is no string value.
 295     """
 296 
 297     if isinstance(path, (six.string_types, bytes)):
 298         return path
 299     path_type = type(path)
 300     try:
 301         path_repr = path_type.__fspath__(path)
 302     except AttributeError:
 303         return
 304     if isinstance(path_repr, (six.string_types, bytes)):
 305         return path_repr
 306     return

 309 # copied from the os backport which in turn copied this from
 310 # the pyutf8 package --
 311 # URL: https://github.com/etrepum/pyutf8/blob/master/pyutf8/ref.py
 312 #
 313 def _invalid_utf8_indexes(bytes):
 314     skips = []
 315     i = 0
 316     len_bytes = len(bytes)
 317     while i < len_bytes:
 318         c1 = bytes[i]
 319         if c1 < 0x80:
 320             # U+0000 - U+007F - 7 bits
 321             i += 1
 322             continue
 323         try:
 324             c2 = bytes[i + 1]
 325             if (c1 & 0xE0 == 0xC0) and (c2 & 0xC0 == 0x80):
 326                 # U+0080 - U+07FF - 11 bits
 327                 c = ((c1 & 0x1F) << 6) | (c2 & 0x3F)
 328                 if c < 0x80:  # pragma: no cover
 329                     # Overlong encoding
 330                     skips.extend([i, i + 1])  # pragma: no cover
 331                 i += 2
 332                 continue
 333             c3 = bytes[i + 2]
 334             if (c1 & 0xF0 == 0xE0) and (c2 & 0xC0 == 0x80) and (c3 & 0xC0 == 0x80):
 335                 # U+0800 - U+FFFF - 16 bits
 336                 c = ((((c1 & 0x0F) << 6) | (c2 & 0x3F)) << 6) | (c3 & 0x3F)
 337                 if (c < 0x800) or (0xD800 <= c <= 0xDFFF):
 338                     # Overlong encoding or surrogate.
 339                     skips.extend([i, i + 1, i + 2])
 340                 i += 3
 341                 continue
 342             c4 = bytes[i + 3]
 343             if (
 344                 (c1 & 0xF8 == 0xF0)
 345                 and (c2 & 0xC0 == 0x80)
 346                 and (c3 & 0xC0 == 0x80)
 347                 and (c4 & 0xC0 == 0x80)
 348             ):
 349                 # U+10000 - U+10FFFF - 21 bits
 350                 c = ((((((c1 & 0x0F) << 6) | (c2 & 0x3F)) << 6) | (c3 & 0x3F)) << 6) | (
 351                     c4 & 0x3F
 352                 )
 353                 if (c < 0x10000) or (c > 0x10FFFF):  # pragma: no cover
 354                     # Overlong encoding or invalid code point.
 355                     skips.extend([i, i + 1, i + 2, i + 3])
 356                 i += 4
 357                 continue
 358         except IndexError:
 359             pass
 360         skips.append(i)
 361         i += 1
 362     return skips
 363

 365 # XXX backport: Another helper to support the Python 2 UTF-8 decoding hack.
 366 def _chunks(b, indexes):
 367     i = 0
 368     for j in indexes:
 369         yield b[i:j]
 370         yield b[j : j + 1]
 371         i = j + 1
 372     yield b[i:]

 375 def fs_encode(path):
 376     """Encode a filesystem path to the proper filesystem encoding.
 377 
 378     :param Union[str, bytes] path: A string-like path
 379     :returns: A bytes-encoded filesystem path representation
 380     """
 381 
 382     path = _get_path(path)
 383     if path is None:
 384         raise TypeError("expected a valid path to encode")
 385     if isinstance(path, six.text_type):
 386         if six.PY2:
 387             return b"".join(
 388                 (
 389                     _byte(ord(c) - 0xDC00)
 390                     if 0xDC00 <= ord(c) <= 0xDCFF
 391                     else c.encode(_fs_encoding, _fs_encode_errors)
 392                 )
 393                 for c in path
 394             )
 395         return path.encode(_fs_encoding, _fs_encode_errors)
 396     return path
 397 
 398 
 399 def fs_decode(path):
 400     """Decode a filesystem path using the proper filesystem encoding.
 401 
 402     :param path: The filesystem path to decode from bytes or string
 403     :return: The filesystem path, decoded with the determined encoding
 404     :rtype: Text
 405     """
 406 
 407     path = _get_path(path)
 408     if path is None:
 409         raise TypeError("expected a valid path to decode")
 410     if isinstance(path, six.binary_type):
 411         import array
 412 
 413         indexes = _invalid_utf8_indexes(array.array(str("B"), path))
 414         if six.PY2:
 415             return "".join(
 416                 chunk.decode(_fs_encoding, _fs_decode_errors)
 417                 for chunk in _chunks(path, indexes)
 418             )
 419         if indexes and os.name == "nt":
 420             return path.decode(_fs_encoding, "surrogateescape")
 421         return path.decode(_fs_encoding, _fs_decode_errors)
 422     return path
 423

 425 if sys.version_info[0] < 3:  # pragma: no cover
 426     _fs_encode_errors = "surrogatepass" if sys.platform == "win32" else "surrogateescape"
 427     _fs_decode_errors = "surrogateescape"
 428     _fs_encoding = "utf-8"
 429 else:  # pragma: no cover
 430     _fs_encoding = "utf-8"
 431     _fs_decode_errors = "surrogateescape"
 432     if sys.platform.startswith("win"):
 433         _fs_error_fn = None
 434         _fs_encode_errors = "surrogatepass"
 435     else:
 436         if sys.version_info >= (3, 3):
 437             _fs_encoding = sys.getfilesystemencoding()
 438             if not _fs_encoding:
 439                 _fs_encoding = sys.getdefaultencoding()
 440         alt_strategy = "surrogateescape"
 441         _fs_error_fn = getattr(sys, "getfilesystemencodeerrors", None)
 442         _fs_encode_errors = _fs_error_fn() if _fs_error_fn else alt_strategy
 443         _fs_decode_errors = _fs_error_fn() if _fs_error_fn else _fs_decode_errors
 444 
 445 _byte = chr if sys.version_info < (3,) else lambda i: bytes([i])
